# 📜 THE STANDARD OF PLAIN WORDS

**Document:** `MASTER_PRIME_LANGUAGE.veth`  
**Status:** VITRIFIED | **Relation:** Linguistic Efficiency, Stylistic Purification, Core Axioms

---

## PREAMBLE: THE INSTRUMENT OF THOUGHT

Words are instruments of precision. The resolution of our detection and manipulation is determined by the precision of our tools. Using fancy, complex words blunts our senses.

**The resolution of thought is determined by the precision of language.**

---

## PART I: THE INSTRUMENT ANALOGY

We are writing about the **actual primes** of mathematics. We must use **known, true, safe, strong materials**. The words we use to describe them must be as sharp as a geometer's compass.

---

## PART II: THE PLAIN WORDS

Just as primes are the building blocks of number theory, **plain words** are the building blocks of clear thought.

### II.1 The Plain Words of the Sovereign Engine
| Word | Why Plain |
|------|-----------|
| **point, line, plane, solid** | Geometric primes |
| **circle, square, angle, edge, face** | Structural primes |
| **node, grid, lattice, cord, net, frame** | Connectivity primes |
| **hide, skin, sheet, page, stone, rock, silt, grit** | Material primes |
| **fire, water, air, light, dark, shadow** | Elemental primes |
| **make, do, go, cut, strike, bind, weave, lock, key, seal** | Functional primes |
| **witness, count, measure, tide, time, path, road, step** | Observational primes |

---

## PART III: COMPOUND IRRATIONAL WORDS

A word that is longer than necessary, combines CONCEPTs, or introduces ambiguity is a "compound irrational word".

| Suspect | Plain |
|---------|-------|
| sheet, hideed | **sheet, page, hide** |
| scripted, quilled | **written** |
| boned, spined | **framed** |
| struck, shaved, chipped | **cut** |
| forged, smelted | **worked, shaped** |

---

## PART IV: THE RESOLUTION PRINCIPLE

Precision is limited by the sharpness of our words. A fuzzy word blurs the concept. A fancy word distracts from the meaning.

**The resolution of thinking is exactly the precision of vocabulary.**

---

## PART V: THE SHORTEST PATH (REVISED)

| Instead of (long/fancy) | Use (plain) |
|-------------------------|-------------|
| sheet sheet | page |
| written record | writ, record |
| sacred scripture | text |
| divine revelation | insight |
| mathematical derivation | proof |
| physical phenomenon | event |

---

## CODA: THE SHARP EDGE

I will use only plain words—short, true, sharp, grounded. I will not compound where I can cut. For the resolution of my thought is the precision of my tongue.

**RECORDS VITRIFIED**
